				\begin{document}$$ \text{VR}\__{w,j} = \sum\limits_{i = 1}^{16} {P_{i} \cdot \text{VR}\__{500,i,j} } , $$\end{document}where P
i represents the annual probability of winds approaching the study area from the wind direction (i), and VR_500,i,j represents the directional wind velocity ratio of the jth test point, the mean wind speed at 2 m above the ground with respect to the reference at 500 m (HKPD 2008). VR_500,i,j is defined as (HKPD 2008):2.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
