				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \text{VR}\__{500,i,j} = \frac{{V\__{p,i,j} }}{{V\__{500,i} }} $$\end{document}where V_
p,i,j represents the mean wind speed of the jth test point at the pedestrian level (2 m above the ground) for wind direction (i), and V_
500,i represents the mean wind speed of the jth test point at 500 m for wind direction (i).

As emphasized in Fig. 2.9, if study areas in wind tunnel experiment were crossed by grids in the map, the average of λ
f(z) for the study areas is calculated by
